caption: I tried this spot before with a friend and I am addicted ever since. I loved the awesome character and flavorful food and drinks. They never disappoint.

Ladies are fast and friendly. Appears cash only. If you’re lucky, on a nice day you can take it to go and enjoy at Seward Park.

Cheap delicious dumplings with an incredibly friendly staff. The nice lady working the register accidentally charged too much but I don't even care it was still ridiculously cheap. I dropped some of my dumplings on the ground though and now I would like to stop existing. 5 stars.

As I was reaching to get my cash only payment ready the lady made a rude comment in chinese "oh look she doesn't even have her payment ready" to another staff making dumplings. I just literally walked in. Give me 1 minute to pull out my waller. If you make comments like that thinking your customers wouldn't understand I dont think you deserve  customers. I used to recommend my coworkers to buy and visit from here but now I dont feel it's fair incase my non asian coworkers to get judged without them knowing.

I personally dislike squeezing hot sauce in my container. Either way. Price. Location. Convenient location. All makeup my 4 stars

This was one of my go to spots for lunch when I was in High-school.  Just last night I came to North Dumplings with my boyfriend, as we were getting to the place it looked like they were closing because a man was outside lowering the gate. I checked the time to make sure it wasn't 10pm. It was 30 minutes to 10pm. We asked the man if they were closed and he was going to say yes but then asked the lady inside and she allowed us to come in. We wanted an order of 20 dumplings, 10 for each of us and she quickly said something and the only thing I understood was that she was going to put a spring roll to substitute for the dumplings.  When my boyfriend and I got to our place we realized that I got 9 dumplings, he got 6 dumplings and a spring roll. We paid about $6.00  It was unrealistic to expect them to have that much dumplings late at night when they are about to close. I just wish they did. I'll just come back during the afternoon when they have a sufficient amount of dumplings.

I was just grabbing something to tide me over while walking around the area but I definitely want to come back and try some of the other things that people have reviewed like the sesame pancakes, noodle soups etc. the ladies working there were super friendly and I hope people keep supporting this neighborhood gem!

The scallion pancakes are also good, if a little bland, compared to the sesame pancakes. The veggie steamed dumplings are okay but possibly better pan fried. The dumplings have a thick skin. Could be the style of the region of China the employees are from. Personally, I prefer thin skinned dumplings and not a big fan of dumplings here. The service was fast and friendly. The space has 2 tables with 4 spots each and a counter with 5 spots. Not fancy at all, but the pancakes are among the best in NYC.

The place is not that clean looking mostly due to the decor and age of the building. They have soup noodles and sesame pancakes also. 4 fried dumps for a $1.25. If I could give a 0-star rating, I would. NEVER GO HERE! I ordered the chive pancakes, pork fried dumplings (for my boyfriend) and vegetable dumplings for myself. I have been a vegetarian and have been for many years, so when I have pork I get physically ill. I came home after eating my dumplings and realized I was given pork, so my boyfriend went back to exchange it for the vegetable ones we ordered. He was eventually screamed at by the worker and she told him that she gave us pork (SO DANGEROUS AND IRRESPONSIBILE FOR MANY REASONS) because we didn't give her enough money. I went in, asking nicely for vegetable dumplings and was SCREAMED AT IMMEDIATELY. She claimed to me that I ordered the pork and I nicely tried to explain that I'm a vegetarian and can't eat pork because it makes me sick, so there is no way I ordered the pork. She kept screaming saying she'll lose money and that we didn't pay for it, IT WAS ONLY A 50 CENT DIFFERENCE. They were completely rude and extreme about the whole situation to the point where they THREW THE PORK DUMPLINGS AT ME AND EMPTIED OUT MY POCKETS TO MAKE ME PROVE I DIDN'T HAVE THE 50 CENTS ON ME TO PAY THE DIFFERENCE. I have NEVER had such a horrible experience.

Yeah, it's not the cleanest place (it's not gross, either). Sure there's barely any place to sit. But the food is mind-numbingly good (my mouth quite literally started to salivate the moment I took a bite out of the first chives and pork steamed dumpling), and it is hilariously, almost unbelievably cheap. Like, I ordered 10 chives and pork steamed dumplings, 4 spring rolls, and 2 pancakes, plus one can of soda, and it cost me a grand total of... $9.50. That's food for two persons, for less than 10 bucks, in Manhattan.  Summary: if you like small, ethnic, hole-in-the-wall places, come here ASAP, you won't regret it.

Was staying nearby while visiting NYC and found via Google Maps. Seem to bleed money when in this city, so wanted something cheap for dinner. Our order for four: 1x spring rolls (4), 1x sesame pancakes (2), 1x chive pancakes (2), 1x large won ton soup, 1x large sweet and sour soup, 2x pan fried pork dumplings (20), 1x steamed veggie dumplings (10, 1x kimchi, and 2 cans of Pepsi, for a grand total of - drumroll please - $25. Whaaaaat????? Everything was fresh and delicious. The sesame pancakes were in fact divine. The kimchi and s&s soup could have been more sour, but that’s a tiny inconvenience. Attached is a photo of our leftovers. Highly recommend!

I travel all the way from Harlem to get these delicious dumplings. I've seen other places charge $7 for 5 dumplings, even $8.99 for 6 and I can't justify that amount. Dumplings shouldn't be complicated, these are perfect. It's a small place unassuming place that is definitely worth the visit. I suggest doing a take out order, there is no seating for large groups, 2 tables that seat 4 and a short bar with stools. We both had a double take and asked if we owed them more and if a mistake was made... Delicious all around and worth the trip. Small, very small inside, with very limited seating so heads up.
